findings.title: Owner privileges (In the period when the owner is not renounced)
findings.description: The contract owner has excessive privileges even after ownership renouncement, allowing them to change various parameters and settings.

findings.title: Unlimited owner capabilities
findings.description: The owner has unlimited capabilities to change various parameters and settings, including tax and liquidity fees, maximum transaction amounts, marketing and buyback divisors, and more. This could lead to potential security issues if the ownership is not properly renounced.

findings.title: Centralization risk due to owner control
findings.description: The contract has centralization risks due to the owner having excessive control over various parameters and functions.

findings.title: Lack of access control for critical functions
